2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper deals with fiber-optical channels, which is a communication and networking topic. 
3. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper proposes a low-complexity detector, which involves optimization and control techniques to reduce complexity.
4. cs.PHYS (Physics): The paper deals with fiber-optical channels, which is a physics topic. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a detector that uses simple straight-line decision boundaries, which involves data structures and algorithms.
